=== Verb ===

'''to clear'''

#To remove [[obstruction]]s or [[impediment]]s.
#:'''''Clear''' the way''.
#To eliminate ambiguity or doubt form a matter; to [[clarify]]; especially, to [[clear up]].
#To pass without interference; to [[miss]].
#:''The door just barely '''clears''' the table as it closes.''
#(of a [[check]]) To go through as [[payment]]; to be [[process]]ed so that the money is transferred.
#:''The check might not '''clear''' for a couple of days.''

